<ext_description linkend="Document_properties_arm.Numerical_document_property">
A <b>Numerical_document_property</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="measure_representation:arm:Measure_representation_arm.Numerical_item_with_unit"/> that specifies a numerical characteristic of a  
  <express_ref
    linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>
or of a
    <express_ref
      linkend="file_identification:arm:File_identification_arm.File"/>.   
  <example number="1">
    The size of a digital file expressed in Megabytes is an example of <express_ref linkend="document_properties:arm:Document_properties_arm.Numerical_document_property"/>.
  </example>
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Document_properties_arm.Numerical_document_property.valued_characteristic">
the <express_ref linkend="document_properties:arm:Document_properties_arm.Document_property_representation"/> that contains the <express_ref linkend="document_properties:arm:Document_properties_arm.Numerical_document_property"/>.
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Document_properties_arm.valid_document_property_representation">The <b>valid_document_property_representation</b> function checks whether the items of a <express_ref linkend="document_properties:arm:Document_properties_arm.Document_property_representation"/> are consistent with the name of the representation.
<p>
It returns True if the representation has a name listed in the predefined list of names and if its items have all a name that belongs to the predefined lists of document characteristic names.
</p>
<p>
It returns Unknown if the representation has not a name listed in the predefined list of <express_ref linkend="document_properties:arm:Document_properties_arm.Document_property_representation"/> names.
</p>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Document_properties_arm.valid_document_property_representation.rep">
the <express_ref linkend="document_properties:arm:Document_properties_arm.Document_property_representation"/> that is evaluated.
</ext_description>
